dataset.title: Wisconsin Regional Trauma Advisory Council (RTCA) Regions
dataset.description:
This dataset contains boundaries for the Wisconsin Regional Trauma Advisory Councils. DHS 118.04 authorizes the department to organize and structure Regional Trauma Advisory Councils (RTACs) and to approve the designation of all trauma care geographic regions based on consideration that represents the best care of trauma patients. The RTACs are structured to be self-directed work groups focusing on regional needs and to improve the care of trauma patients and their families.

For more information please visit the Wisconsin Department of Health Services website: https://www.dhs.wisconsin.gov/wish/injury-mortality/rtac.htm

dataset.title: Wisconsin Bureau of Nursing Home Resident Care (BNHRC) Regions
dataset.description:
This dataset contains boundaries for the Bureau of Nursing Home Resident Care regions. The Bureau of Nursing Home Resident Care (BNHRC) is responsible for conducting unannounced health care surveys of nursing homes and facilities serving persons with developmental disabilities (FDDs - also known as Intermediate Care Facilities for Individuals with Intellectual Disabilities, ICF/IID).

For more information please visit the Wisconsin Department of Health Services website: https://www.dhs.wisconsin.gov/dqa/bnhrc-regionalmap.htm
keyword: Bureau of Nursing Home Resident Care

dataset.title: Wisconsin FoodShare Employment and Training (FSET) Regions
dataset.description:
This dataset contains boundaries for the FoodShare Employment and Training regions. The FoodShare Employment and Training (FSET) program is a free program that helps FoodShare members build their job skills and find jobs. There are eleven FSET regions. Each FSET region coordinates FSET services for the residents of counties located in that region.

For more information please visit the Wisconsin Department of Health Services website: https://www.dhs.wisconsin.gov/fset/fset-regions.htm

dataset.title: Wisconsin Public Health Regions
dataset.description:
This dataset contains boundaries for the Wisconsin Public Health Regions. Public Health Regions are used to coordinate staff and resources for the Division of Public Health. Resources and staff are organized by Public Health regions and provide contract monitoring, technical assistance, and training related to public health infrastructure, family and community health, communicable disease prevention and control, chronic disease prevention and health promotion, environmental health, and injury prevention.

For more information please visit the Wisconsin Department of Health Services website: https://www.dhs.wisconsin.gov/lh-depts/counties.htm

dataset.title: Wisconsin Income Maintenance Regions
dataset.description:
This dataset contains boundaries for the Wisconsin Income Maintenance Consortia. The Wisconsin Department of Health Services partners with counties and tribes to provide eligibility services for people who are applying for or are enrolled in programs like Medicaid, BadgerCare Plus, and FoodShare. County agencies that provide eligibility services are often called income maintenance or economic support agencies. These county agencies have joined together to form 11 consortium across the state.

For more information please visit the Wisconsin Department of Health Services website: https://www.dhs.wisconsin.gov/forwardhealth/imagency/index.htm

dataset.title: Wisconsin Healthcare Emergency Readiness Coalition Regions
dataset.description:
This dataset contains the boundaries for the Wisconsin Healthcare Emergency Readiness Coalition regions. In 2014, Wisconsin established seven healthcare coalition regions to coordinate how public health, healthcare institutions, and first responder agencies, such as police, fire and emergency medical services (EMS), will manage their efforts to enact a uniform and unified response to an emergency, including a mass casualty or other catastrophic event.

For more information please visit the Wisconsin Department of Health Services website: https://www.dhs.wisconsin.gov/preparedness/healthcare/index.htm

dataset.title: Wisconsin Family Care Geographic Service Regions
dataset.description:
This dataset contains boundaries for the Family Care Geographic Service Regions. Family Care is a Medicaid long-term care program for frail elders, and adults with physical, developmental, or intellectual disabilities. People in the program receive long-term care services to help them live in their own home whenever possible.

For more information please visit the Wisconsin Department of Health Services website: https://www.dhs.wisconsin.gov/familycare/index.htm

dataset.title: Wisconsin Area Administration Regions
dataset.description:
This dataset contains boundaries for the Wisconsin DHS Area Administration regions. Area Administration Regions are a function of the Wisconsin Department of Health Services to be used for reference and resource allocation of WI DHS Area Administration resources and programs.

For more information please visit the Wisconsin Department of Health Services website: https://www.dhs.wisconsin.gov/areaadmin/index.htm

dataset.title: Wisconsin Program of All-Inclusive Care for the Elderly (PACE) Regions
dataset.description:
This dataset contains boundaries for the Program of All-Inclusive Care regions. The Program of All-Inclusive Care for the Elderly, also known as PACE, provides a full range of long-term care, health care, and prescription drugs to older people with chronic needs.

For more information please visit the Wisconsin Department of Health Services website: https://www.dhs.wisconsin.gov/familycare/pace.htm
keyword: Programs of All-Inclusive Care for the Elderly

dataset.title: Wisconsin Division of Public Health Regional Offices
dataset.description:
This dataset contains the point locations of the Division of Public Health regional offices in Wisconsin. The Division of Public Health (DPH) works with our local and tribal public health partners, and community groups statewide, on a wide variety of programs and services that protect the health of Wisconsin residents.

For more information please visit the Wisconsin Department of Health Services website: https://www.dhs.wisconsin.gov/dph/index.htm

dataset.title: Wisconsin Nurse Aide Training Programs
dataset.description:
This dataset contains locations and attributes of Nurse Aide Training Programs approved by the state of Wisconsin. The data is used for planning, management and analysis by Wisconsin Department of Health Services staff and other government agencies. Nurse Aide Training Programs are training sites/programs/instructors approved by the Division of Quality Assurance (DQA) to train certified nursing assistants (CNAs) that will have the credentials needed to work in DQA-regulated health care facilities such as nursing homes. They can be affiliated with/run by licensed health care facilities or stand-alone programs.

For more information, please visit the Wisconsin Department of Health Services website: https://www.dhs.wisconsin.gov/caregiver/nurse-aide/index.htm

dataset.title: Wisconsin Environmental Public Health Tracking
dataset.description:
Wisconsin Environmental Public Health Tracking is your source for environmental health data in Wisconsin.

COMPREHENSIVE.

We house data on nearly a dozen environmental public health topics such as air quality, asthma, Lyme disease, and many others.

CURRENT.

We work with data managers to host the most up-to-date data available.

EASY.

Our data portal has improved mapping, exporting, mobility, and the capacity to display data below the county-level. Note that the portal works best with Firefox and Chrome web browsers.

dataset.title: Flood Risk Map
dataset.description: The Wisconsin Department of Health Services, along with several partnering agencies, has created the Wisconsin Flood Risk Mapping Application (WFRMA) to provide accurate, authoritative, and relevant spatial data resources for emergency preparedness and planning efforts.

dataset.title: Immunization Map
dataset.description: This map displays the student immunization information reported from Wisconsin schools for the 2017-2018 school year.

dataset.title: Radon Map
dataset.description: The radon data displayed in the map represent over 100,000 Wisconsin indoor radon test results conducted from 1995 to 2016. The test results are geocoded and aggregated to ZIP code boundaries. The radon values are reported in picocurries per liter (pCi/L).
dataset.license: https://data.dhsgis.wi.gov/pages/gis-data-disclaimer

dataset.title: Wisconsin Heat Vulnerability Index
dataset.description: The Wisconsin Heat Vulnerability Index (HVI) is based on multiple indicators associated with risk for heat related illness and mortality. The index analysis was created as a measure of vulnerability by U.S. Census block groups during an extreme heat-related event. The measure includes health factors, demographic and household characteristics, natural and built environment factors (e.g. air quality, temperature, land cover) and population density.
